# Resonant LR Modem Firmware (Heltec V3)

## Hardware
- Heltec WiFi LoRa 32 V3: ESP32-S3 + SX1262 + WiFi, always-on (mains powered)
- Dual-core: Core 0 = radio, Core 1 = WiFi + MQTT + web server
- Serial for debug output (USB CDC)

## Role
Transparent LoRa↔MQTT bridge. Does NOT decrypt — forwards raw frames to gateway software.

## Core Architecture
- `backgroundTasks()` on Core 0: radio init, `resonantRadio.loop()`
- `loop()` on Core 1: web server, WiFi reconnect, MQTT, RX event processing
- RX events: Core 0 callback → `rxEventSlot` → Core 1 processes → MQTT publish
- Continuous RX mode — always listening after TX completes

## MQTT Topics
- `modems/{modem_id}` — health/status (retained)
- `{modem_id}/{device_id}/data` — uplink data from devices
- `{modem_id}` — downlink commands (subscribe)
- `{modem_id}/config` — remote configuration (subscribe)
- `{modem_id}/config/ack` — config acknowledgment (publish)

## Key Patterns
- Single-packet: publish raw frame bytes (rxRawFrameBuffer)
- Multi-packet: publish reassembled payload, extract inner frame type
- Downlink: JSON `{destination_id: [4 bytes], data: [frame bytes]}` → radio.send()
- Config: JSON with wifi_ssid, mqtt_host, lora_freq, etc. → save + apply
- Web UI on port 80 for local configuration
- NVS persistence for all settings
- lib_ignore: RESONANT_POWER_MANAGER, RESONANT_STORAGE

## Build & Deploy
```
pio run -t upload          # compile and flash
pio run -t monitor         # serial monitor (115200 baud)
```
Upload port: /dev/tty.usbserial-0001
